WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.419
<i>Previously on</i> This Is Us...

00:02.502 --> 00:04.129
<i>JAE-WON: Today's bulletin--</i>

00:04.212 --> 00:05.672
<i>it's kind of going viral.</i>

00:05.755 --> 00:07.298
<i>I'm doing this for William Hill.</i>

00:07.382 --> 00:09.175
<i>Because you all were his family.</i>

00:09.259 --> 00:11.636
<i>"My name's Hai Lang,</i>
<i>and I live in New Orleans.</i>

00:11.720 --> 00:14.556
"I believe I knew your mother, Laurel.

00:14.639 --> 00:15.974
"I was by her side when she died

00:16.057 --> 00:17.600
in May of 2015."

00:17.684 --> 00:18.893
What?

00:18.977 --> 00:19.978
I wish I could show you

00:20.061 --> 00:21.271
<i>the places she lived,</i>

00:21.354 --> 00:22.605
<i>the things she loved.</i>

00:22.689 --> 00:24.274
Hey, what if we were to come out there?

00:24.357 --> 00:26.568
If that's what you could do.

00:28.570 --> 00:30.280
♪ ♪

00:35.660 --> 00:38.079
You okay, babe?

00:38.163 --> 00:40.749
You haven't said much
since we got in last night.

00:40.832 --> 00:43.376
I'm just thinking about
the last time we were here.

00:43.460 --> 00:45.003
Mm. Our fifth anniversary.

00:45.086 --> 00:47.547
Oh, we tried absinthe for the first time.

00:48.882 --> 00:50.675
That was a good night.

00:50.759 --> 00:52.218
Five-hour man.

00:52.302 --> 00:53.678
It was six.

00:53.762 --> 00:57.098
-Don't short-change a brother.
-Oh, okay. My fault.

00:57.182 --> 00:58.975
We were here for... what?

00:59.059 --> 01:00.602
-Five, six days?
-Mm-hmm.

01:02.062 --> 01:04.397
Could've walked right past her
and wouldn't have even known it.

01:22.791 --> 01:24.793
♪ ♪

01:32.217 --> 01:33.551
Randall.

01:33.635 --> 01:36.304
Welcome.

01:36.388 --> 01:38.390
It's nice to finally meet you in person.

01:38.473 --> 01:39.516
RANDALL: It's a pleasure.

01:39.599 --> 01:41.267
Thank you for agreeing to this.

01:41.351 --> 01:43.853
And thank you
for testing and quarantining.

01:43.937 --> 01:45.939
-I know it's a lot to ask.
-Not at all.

01:46.022 --> 01:47.774
You remember my wife, Beth?

01:47.857 --> 01:50.068
Your place is beautiful.

01:50.151 --> 01:52.404
It's, uh, actually yours.

01:52.487 --> 01:54.155
Excuse me?

01:54.239 --> 01:55.448
This house,

01:55.532 --> 01:57.492
this land...

01:57.575 --> 01:58.952
it was your mother's.

01:59.035 --> 02:00.912
And now it's yours.

02:02.372 --> 02:03.790
Come in.

02:06.626 --> 02:09.004
(quietly):
I'm gonna need some absinthe tonight.

02:12.340 --> 02:14.342
♪ ♪

02:18.263 --> 02:21.057
You must have a million questions.

02:21.141 --> 02:24.019
A million is in the ballpark, yes.

02:25.270 --> 02:27.647
I'll tell you what I know,

02:27.731 --> 02:29.107
from the beginning.

02:33.028 --> 02:35.363
Your mother was a Dubois.

02:35.447 --> 02:38.908
They were the most distinguished
family in town.

02:38.992 --> 02:40.785
-(light laughter)
<i>-HAI: I think that was always</i>

02:40.869 --> 02:42.829
<i>a lot of pressure on Laurel.</i>

02:42.912 --> 02:44.539
ELIZABETH: Oh, stop.

02:44.622 --> 02:46.875
I'll check the guest list,
but I think we should go.

02:46.958 --> 02:48.960
Elizabeth, I said I'd think about it.

02:49.044 --> 02:51.338
I don't want to think about it right now.

02:51.421 --> 02:53.048
(sighs) Hilda, my briefcase.

02:54.591 --> 02:56.009
You're going to the bank on Sunday?

02:56.092 --> 02:58.178
It's such a lovely day out,

02:58.261 --> 03:00.388
I thought we might take a stroll
after lunch.

03:00.472 --> 03:02.515
Laurel...

03:02.599 --> 03:05.310
What is it I always say?

03:08.188 --> 03:10.357
You need to start paying
more attention during Mass,

03:10.440 --> 03:11.608
young lady.

03:11.691 --> 03:13.234
Jackson...

03:13.318 --> 03:14.319
"To whomever much is given,

03:14.402 --> 03:15.653
much will be required."

03:15.737 --> 03:17.364
Luke 12:48.

03:17.447 --> 03:18.490
PAUL: Very good.

03:20.241 --> 03:22.243
Um, Elizabeth, honey.

03:22.327 --> 03:24.329
If I get back before supper,

03:24.412 --> 03:25.580
maybe we'll take that stroll.

03:25.663 --> 03:26.956
Mwah.

03:27.040 --> 03:29.250
You two, mind your mother.

03:37.175 --> 03:38.635
I've got to lay down.

03:38.718 --> 03:40.470
I do not want to hear the television set

03:40.553 --> 03:43.139
until homework is finished, you hear me?

03:43.223 --> 03:44.182
Yes, ma'am.

03:54.818 --> 03:56.861
You can't let Daddy ruffle your feathers.

03:58.363 --> 03:59.781
(sighs)

03:59.864 --> 04:02.075
Cover for me while I go visit Aunt Mae?

04:02.158 --> 04:03.868
Again?

04:03.952 --> 04:05.328
Well, if you're so worried, come with me.

04:06.621 --> 04:08.832
Then who would sneak you back in
when you got home?

04:08.915 --> 04:10.250
Ah.

04:12.043 --> 04:14.337
Thank you, thank you,
thank you, thank you.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.423
♪ ♪

04:31.187 --> 04:33.314
Mind my peppers.

04:33.398 --> 04:36.943
(sighs) I forgot, you have eyes
in the back of your head.

04:37.027 --> 04:38.987
No, I just know you.

04:39.070 --> 04:41.865
There are two kinds of people
in this world.

04:41.948 --> 04:44.409
The ones who look before they leap,

04:44.492 --> 04:47.370
and the other ones,
who throw their arms out

04:47.454 --> 04:48.955
and plunge into the void,

04:49.039 --> 04:51.249
not the least bit worried
about what's below.

04:51.332 --> 04:53.752
And you, my darling, are the latter.

04:53.835 --> 04:55.462
How do you know?

04:55.545 --> 04:57.797
'Cause I'm the latter, too.
(laughs)

04:57.881 --> 04:59.549
I was fixin' to go for a swim.

04:59.632 --> 05:00.967
-You want to come? All right.
-Mm-hmm.

05:01.051 --> 05:02.594
Help me get those tomatoes inside.

05:02.677 --> 05:04.679
♪ ♪

05:17.233 --> 05:19.736
I know.
I know I'm late.

05:21.029 --> 05:23.239
Mama's gonna have a fit.
Come on.

05:25.658 --> 05:27.660
Laurel, where have you been?

05:28.870 --> 05:32.165
And don't you even
fix your mouth to tell a lie.

05:37.962 --> 05:39.547
Aunt Mae's.

05:40.632 --> 05:41.966
After I forbade you?

05:42.050 --> 05:43.927
I'm sorry, Daddy.

05:44.010 --> 05:46.346
I will not tolerate a disobedient child.

05:46.429 --> 05:48.723
If you even think
about going over there again,

05:48.807 --> 05:50.767
you will get a lashing
you will not soon forget.

05:50.850 --> 05:52.018
Am I clear?

05:53.228 --> 05:55.105
Yes, sir.

06:01.111 --> 06:02.946
-Ow!
-Sit still.

06:03.029 --> 06:05.824
I'll comb the wild out you
if it's the last thing I do.

06:09.577 --> 06:11.579
♪ ♪

06:12.664 --> 06:13.998
Can I hide out in here?

06:14.082 --> 06:16.793
Only if you promise to be quiet.

06:16.876 --> 06:19.421
♪ <i>Why</i> ♪

06:19.504 --> 06:23.049
♪ <i>Should I be</i> ♪

06:23.133 --> 06:25.385
♪ <i>Discouraged...</i> ♪

06:25.468 --> 06:27.095
Don't you have any Marvin Gaye?

06:27.178 --> 06:29.180
Mahalia Jackson sang for MLK.

06:29.264 --> 06:30.306
She's an American queen.

06:30.390 --> 06:33.601
♪ <i>Why</i> ♪

06:33.685 --> 06:37.939
♪ <i>Should the shadows...</i> ♪

06:38.023 --> 06:39.399
You all right?

06:39.482 --> 06:40.817
Yeah.

06:40.900 --> 06:42.861
Just still don't understand

06:42.944 --> 06:45.113
how Daddy could hate his own sister.

06:45.196 --> 06:46.990
Aunt Mae's his blood.

06:48.658 --> 06:50.452
I could never hate you, Jackson.

06:50.535 --> 06:53.621
Other than Aunt Mae,
you're the only one who understands me.

06:53.705 --> 06:56.958
I don't understand you.

06:57.042 --> 06:58.376
Ow.

06:58.460 --> 07:01.004
All right. You ain't even
holding this right, okay?

07:01.087 --> 07:02.255
Let me show you.

07:02.339 --> 07:04.632
♪ <i>And long...</i> ♪

07:04.716 --> 07:06.509
<i>HAI:</i>
<i>Laurel hated being away from Aunt Mae.</i>

07:06.593 --> 07:09.512
<i>But she had Jackson.</i>

07:09.596 --> 07:11.765
<i>And when he went to fight in Vietnam,</i>

07:11.848 --> 07:15.518
she said she never felt so alone.

07:15.602 --> 07:17.687
♪ ♪

07:17.771 --> 07:22.400
♪ <i>When Jesus</i> ♪

07:22.484 --> 07:25.153
♪ <i>Is</i> ♪

07:26.488 --> 07:29.783
♪ <i>My portion</i> ♪

07:32.619 --> 07:36.081
♪ <i>And my constant</i> ♪

07:36.164 --> 07:39.709
♪ <i>Friend</i> ♪

07:39.793 --> 07:44.005
♪ <i>Is he</i> ♪

07:47.676 --> 07:49.052
(engine approaches)

07:49.135 --> 07:51.429
-♪ <i>You know his eye</i> ♪
-(engine shuts off)

07:51.513 --> 07:53.223
(car doors open, close)

07:53.306 --> 07:55.141
♪ <i>Is on</i> ♪

07:55.225 --> 07:56.643
(doorbell rings)

07:56.726 --> 08:00.480
♪ <i>Little old sparrow</i> ♪

08:03.316 --> 08:07.862
♪ <i>And I know</i> ♪

08:07.946 --> 08:10.657
♪ <i>He cares</i> ♪

08:10.740 --> 08:15.203
♪ <i>For you and me</i> ♪

08:15.286 --> 08:17.247
♪ ♪

08:17.330 --> 08:21.251
♪ <i>His eye...</i> ♪

08:22.752 --> 08:24.671
LAUREL:
I can't believe he's gone.

08:29.259 --> 08:32.095
Jackson is really gone.

08:34.848 --> 08:37.642
What am I gonna do without him?

08:39.978 --> 08:43.189
God can take your pain...

08:45.191 --> 08:46.943
...my sweet Laurel.

08:51.072 --> 08:53.408
But you have to let it go.

08:57.328 --> 08:59.414
I don't know how.

09:05.587 --> 09:06.755
There.

09:09.007 --> 09:11.968
I go in there,

09:12.052 --> 09:14.512
and let it all out.

09:14.596 --> 09:15.597
Hmm.

09:19.601 --> 09:21.436
Go on.

09:25.440 --> 09:27.150
Yeah.

09:28.443 --> 09:29.736
Go on.

09:33.448 --> 09:35.450
♪ ♪

09:46.711 --> 09:48.713
(birds singing)

10:11.945 --> 10:13.947
(sniffles)

10:15.990 --> 10:17.534
(screams)

10:28.545 --> 10:30.922
Is it too much?

10:31.006 --> 10:34.050
No, I'm sorry.
I, uh...

10:34.134 --> 10:37.178
I just met and lost an uncle
in the course of five minutes.

10:37.262 --> 10:38.680
BETH:
Hmm.

10:38.763 --> 10:41.016
I, uh, I didn't realize that

10:41.099 --> 10:42.392
you'd know quite so much about her.

10:42.475 --> 10:46.354
How did you know her, exactly?

10:46.438 --> 10:48.440
If I'm being honest,

10:48.523 --> 10:51.026
your mother was the love of my life.

10:56.614 --> 11:00.660
After the war ended,
my family and I became refugees.

11:00.744 --> 11:03.997
The church helped bring a lot of us here.

11:04.080 --> 11:07.083
<i>The weather, the water...</i>

11:07.167 --> 11:09.085
<i>made it a perfect home for us.</i>

11:09.169 --> 11:13.298
<i>I decided to become a fisherman</i>
<i>to care for my parents.</i>

11:13.381 --> 11:17.344
It was out there where I saw
Laurel for the first time.

11:17.427 --> 11:18.887
(laughs softly)
Or should I say,

11:18.970 --> 11:20.680
<i>heard</i> her for the first time.

11:20.764 --> 11:22.390
♪ ♪

11:22.474 --> 11:24.059
Yeah!

11:27.020 --> 11:29.856
(Laurel screaming)

11:52.712 --> 11:54.714
♪ ♪

11:57.509 --> 11:59.219
(screams)

11:59.302 --> 12:00.553
W-Whoa, whoa!

12:00.637 --> 12:02.263
-(stammers)
-What are you doing?!

12:02.347 --> 12:03.682
Get off of me!

12:03.765 --> 12:06.059
Get away from me!

12:06.142 --> 12:07.811
I'm not drowning.

12:12.273 --> 12:13.400
Hmm.

12:13.483 --> 12:15.443
I couldn't stop thinking about the woman

12:15.527 --> 12:17.529
who wasn't drowning.

12:17.612 --> 12:20.448
That's what I called her
before I knew her name.

12:21.908 --> 12:23.952
Before I knew anything.

12:27.831 --> 12:30.458
Oh, Mae, let me get that for you.

12:30.542 --> 12:32.836
These old bones appreciate the help,

12:32.919 --> 12:35.213
but I don't want to get
in the way of you spending time

12:35.296 --> 12:37.090
with that handsome fellow of yours.

12:37.173 --> 12:40.135
Marshall's busy at the bank with Daddy.
As usual.

12:42.303 --> 12:43.471
That's not a complaint.

12:43.555 --> 12:44.472
Any woman in New Orleans

12:44.556 --> 12:46.099
would be lucky to have him.

12:46.182 --> 12:47.517
Mm, so he's a dud.

12:47.600 --> 12:49.561
(laughs)
Aunt Mae, quit!

12:49.644 --> 12:51.855
MAE:
You go and take these over to Marcel.

12:51.938 --> 12:53.898
If he tries to pay for 'em,
don't take his money.

12:53.982 --> 12:56.651
-Yes, ma'am.
-Mm-hmm.

12:58.361 --> 13:00.864
-Hi, Mr. Leblanc.
-Good morning, Miss Dubois.

13:00.947 --> 13:02.240
Morning.

13:05.243 --> 13:06.911
Hey.

13:06.995 --> 13:08.288
It's you.

13:08.371 --> 13:10.874
It's you from the lake.

13:10.957 --> 13:12.876
(speaks Vietnamese)

13:12.959 --> 13:14.711
What?

13:19.924 --> 13:22.260
-(Laurel laughs)
-Aah!

13:22.344 --> 13:23.386
(laughing)

13:23.470 --> 13:24.888
You. "Aah!"

13:24.971 --> 13:27.015
(laughs):
Yeah, that was me.

13:27.098 --> 13:28.600
But I wasn't drowning.

13:30.852 --> 13:33.063
I'm Laurel.

13:33.146 --> 13:34.731
Hai.

13:34.814 --> 13:36.149
Hello.

13:36.232 --> 13:38.443
No.

13:38.526 --> 13:39.694
Hai.

13:39.778 --> 13:41.654
Oh.

13:41.738 --> 13:44.282
That's your name.

13:44.366 --> 13:46.409
Nice to meet you.

13:47.911 --> 13:49.079
(Laurel laughs softly)

13:58.296 --> 13:59.506
Uh, for me?

14:00.799 --> 14:03.885
I... I'm not much of a cook.

14:05.512 --> 14:06.596
-(laughs)
-Oh.

14:06.680 --> 14:09.265
Um, bad cook.

14:10.600 --> 14:12.560
We...
(imitates choking)

14:12.644 --> 14:14.771
(laughs):
Oh! Yeah.

14:14.854 --> 14:17.315
-Uh-huh.
-Yeah.

14:19.484 --> 14:21.486
I cook.

14:21.569 --> 14:23.655
You eat?

14:27.325 --> 14:28.993
Okay.

14:30.787 --> 14:33.790
♪ ♪

14:36.292 --> 14:39.754
<i>HAI:</i>
<i>I still remember the look in her eyes.</i>

14:43.967 --> 14:46.845
♪ ♪

14:50.515 --> 14:51.891
<i>Being with her...</i>

14:51.975 --> 14:53.852
Pinch the tail.

14:53.935 --> 14:55.395
Suck the head.

14:56.980 --> 14:59.107
-(laughs)
-Mmm.

14:59.190 --> 15:02.902
...was the best time of my life.

15:02.986 --> 15:05.071
ELIZABETH:
It's so nice to have you over, Marshall.

15:06.906 --> 15:09.617
<i>HAI:</i>
<i>But I know it was complicated for her.</i>

15:15.790 --> 15:18.251
I want to tell you something, but...

15:20.754 --> 15:23.131
...don't make fun of me, okay?

15:24.215 --> 15:26.676
-What?
-(laughs)

15:32.766 --> 15:34.392
<i>Em yêu anh.</i>

15:37.062 --> 15:39.022
<i>Anh yêu em.</i>

15:40.815 --> 15:43.318
I love you, too.

15:43.401 --> 15:45.403
♪ ♪

16:00.043 --> 16:02.045
(insects chirping)

16:17.060 --> 16:18.728
PAUL:
Laurel.

16:27.320 --> 16:29.072
(opera music playing over radio)

16:29.155 --> 16:30.949
Daddy, I didn't know you were up.

16:32.909 --> 16:34.911
It's after midnight.

16:34.994 --> 16:37.539
Oh, I was studying at Dorothy's.

16:37.622 --> 16:38.915
Then we went into the city.

16:38.998 --> 16:40.083
Must've lost track of time.

16:40.166 --> 16:41.918
Mm.

16:42.002 --> 16:43.503
Yeah.

16:43.586 --> 16:44.963
-Come on.
-(pats chair)

16:50.301 --> 16:53.138
You know, I feel like
I hardly even see you

16:53.221 --> 16:55.807
at dinner these last few weeks.

16:55.890 --> 16:57.892
My studies have been keeping me busy.

16:57.976 --> 16:59.853
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

16:59.936 --> 17:01.730
Marshall told me as much.

17:04.899 --> 17:06.651
I offered him
the vice president's position

17:06.735 --> 17:08.069
at the bank.

17:08.153 --> 17:10.196
Oh, that's wonderful.

17:10.280 --> 17:12.490
-I'm happy for him.
-Mm. Yeah.

17:12.574 --> 17:14.576
He plans to propose.

17:14.659 --> 17:17.620
I've already given him my blessing.

17:17.704 --> 17:20.123
Quite frankly, it was an easy yes.

17:21.458 --> 17:23.168
(Paul sighs)

17:23.251 --> 17:26.171
Now, the reason I'm telling you
all of this

17:26.254 --> 17:29.424
is because Marshall
is coming over for dinner

17:29.507 --> 17:31.509
to celebrate his promotion.

17:33.219 --> 17:35.972
Should he decide to propose...

17:37.140 --> 17:39.851
...your answer will be an easy yes.

17:44.147 --> 17:47.108
♪ ♪

17:59.913 --> 18:01.581
Laurel?

18:01.664 --> 18:03.875
I can't be here one more day.

18:03.958 --> 18:06.920
Let's leave.
I-I know people in Chicago.

18:07.003 --> 18:08.922
We can go now.

18:09.005 --> 18:12.008
We can be together, freely,
like we always wanted.

18:12.092 --> 18:14.761
I love you, Hai.

18:14.844 --> 18:16.304
Come with me.

18:20.975 --> 18:23.687
<i>HAI:</i>
<i>I knew her father would not let us</i>

18:23.770 --> 18:26.356
<i>be together, and I wanted to go with her.</i>

18:26.439 --> 18:30.110
<i>But my parents would not</i>
<i>have survived without me.</i>

18:30.193 --> 18:32.278
I cannot.

18:33.947 --> 18:36.241
S-Stay with me.

18:37.951 --> 18:39.703
Please.

18:41.788 --> 18:43.498
I can't.

18:56.302 --> 18:57.595
(car door closes)

18:57.679 --> 18:58.763
So she went to Chicago?

19:00.890 --> 19:02.475
She never made it.

19:02.559 --> 19:04.436
The cheapest bus out was to Pittsburgh.

19:04.519 --> 19:06.104
And that's when she met William
and had me?

19:06.187 --> 19:07.439
Eventually.

19:07.522 --> 19:09.983
She needed time to adjust to the city,

19:10.066 --> 19:11.735
-find her place.
-Okay.

19:11.818 --> 19:13.903
Look, um...

19:13.987 --> 19:15.321
we've come a long way.

19:15.405 --> 19:17.699
And you have told us a gorgeous story.

19:17.782 --> 19:20.577
-Seriously, it rivals <i>The Notebook.</i>
-Randall, just let him finish.

19:20.660 --> 19:22.579
All I really want to know
is why William told me

19:22.662 --> 19:24.456
my mother died of an overdose
after having me.

19:24.539 --> 19:27.208
Now, you said on the phone
that he was telling the truth.

19:27.292 --> 19:30.003
But how?
Like, why did he think she died?

19:30.086 --> 19:32.005
Because she did.

19:32.088 --> 19:33.965
What?

19:34.049 --> 19:36.676
Hai, we're gonna
need a little more than that.

19:36.760 --> 19:39.304
The nurses told Laurel she OD'd.

19:39.387 --> 19:41.181
<i>She was unresponsive.</i>

19:41.264 --> 19:43.475
MEDIC:
Joel, leave her.

19:43.558 --> 19:45.226
-(Randall coos)
-I-Is she gone?

19:45.310 --> 19:47.354
MEDIC:
Mark the time and call it in.

19:47.437 --> 19:49.522
<i>HAI: The paramedics said</i>
<i>when they were trying to revive her,</i>

19:49.606 --> 19:51.691
<i>your father took you and ran.</i>

19:51.775 --> 19:53.651
So that's it?

19:53.735 --> 19:55.445
I mean, after she got out of the hospital,

19:55.528 --> 19:57.238
why didn't she try to find me?

19:57.322 --> 19:59.449
William didn't just vanish into thin air.

19:59.532 --> 20:02.035
-She was going to.
-Then why didn't she? What stopped her?

20:02.118 --> 20:03.912
Prison.

20:06.164 --> 20:09.626
Please sit.

20:09.709 --> 20:12.253
This isn't <i>The Notebook.</i>

20:20.011 --> 20:21.971
HAI:
Like I said,

20:22.055 --> 20:25.350
Laurel didn't go to prison right away.

20:25.433 --> 20:27.769
<i>She ended up in the hospital.</i>

20:27.852 --> 20:29.437
(monitor beeping steadily)

20:29.521 --> 20:31.648
(weakly):
Where's my baby?

20:31.731 --> 20:33.942
W-Where's my baby?

20:35.193 --> 20:36.861
-Where's my baby?
-Ma'am, please.

20:36.945 --> 20:39.280
-I need you to relax.
-I need my baby.

20:39.364 --> 20:41.991
-Take it easy. Take it easy.
-All right.

20:42.075 --> 20:43.535
William? William?

20:43.618 --> 20:44.744
We don't know where he is, but you

20:44.828 --> 20:46.162
-just need to relax, okay?
-I need my baby.

20:46.246 --> 20:47.414
Take it easy.

20:47.497 --> 20:49.207
-William...
-(shushing)

20:49.290 --> 20:51.334
(shushing)

20:51.418 --> 20:53.420
♪ ♪

20:59.718 --> 21:02.345
NURSE: What kind of mother
gets high after giving birth?

21:02.429 --> 21:05.056
NURSE 2:
Wherever that baby is, he's better off.

21:05.140 --> 21:08.518
♪ <i>The devil's in the basement in my home</i> ♪

21:08.601 --> 21:11.354
<i>HAI: She recovered in the hospital</i>
<i>for a few days.</i>

21:11.438 --> 21:13.857
♪ <i>A flight of stairs is way too close</i> ♪

21:13.940 --> 21:15.275
There she is.

21:15.358 --> 21:16.901
<i>HAI:</i>
<i>Then the police showed up.</i>

21:16.985 --> 21:18.069
♪ <i>He comes for me...</i> ♪

21:18.153 --> 21:19.571
Laurel Dubois?

21:19.654 --> 21:21.656
<i>And she was arrested for drug possession.</i>

21:21.740 --> 21:22.657
There's a warrant out for your arrest.

21:22.741 --> 21:24.159
♪ <i>Collecting debts</i> ♪

21:24.242 --> 21:27.245
♪ <i>That I don't owe</i> ♪

21:28.913 --> 21:31.791
♪ <i>Follow me down</i>
<i>where the waters run deep</i> ♪

21:31.875 --> 21:33.668
We don't have a phone.

21:33.752 --> 21:37.255
I-I need to call my boyfriend,
but we don't have a phone.

21:37.339 --> 21:39.507
There's no one else?
No family?

21:39.591 --> 21:42.260
♪ <i>If my intentions are good, why can't I</i> ♪

21:42.344 --> 21:44.763
♪ <i>Come clean?</i> ♪

21:46.014 --> 21:49.392
♪ <i>If heaven's above,</i>
<i>where does that leave me?</i> ♪

21:52.604 --> 21:55.857
♪ <i>Am I looking</i> ♪

21:55.940 --> 21:59.152
♪ <i>For revival?</i> ♪

21:59.235 --> 22:01.363
♪ <i>Am I dressed in others' sin?</i> ♪

22:01.446 --> 22:03.448
(phone ringing)

22:06.159 --> 22:07.869
Dubois residence.

22:07.952 --> 22:11.998
♪ <i>Hold my breath until I'm honest</i> ♪

22:12.082 --> 22:13.667
Hello?

22:13.750 --> 22:16.461
♪ <i>Will I ever breathe again?</i> ♪

22:19.798 --> 22:21.341
Laurel?

22:21.424 --> 22:23.468
♪ <i>When the world's so heavy</i> ♪

22:23.551 --> 22:27.722
♪ <i>I can't stand</i> ♪

22:27.806 --> 22:31.267
♪ <i>I close my eyes and start again</i> ♪

22:33.520 --> 22:34.813
♪ <i>Though my heart</i> ♪

22:34.896 --> 22:37.899
♪ <i>Is in my hands</i> ♪

22:39.025 --> 22:43.697
♪ <i>I won't break,</i>
<i>give me faith to bend...</i> ♪

22:43.780 --> 22:47.158
<i>HAI:</i>
<i>Laurel's lawyer made her plead guilty.</i>

22:47.242 --> 22:49.411
<i>It was her only offense.</i>

22:49.494 --> 22:51.830
<i>He thought she'd get mercy.</i>

22:51.913 --> 22:54.582
<i>But the judge sentenced her to five years.</i>

22:58.962 --> 23:02.298
The prisons in Pittsburgh
were overcrowded,

23:02.382 --> 23:05.051
so Laurel was sent to California.

23:06.344 --> 23:10.181
♪ <i>Will I ever breathe again?</i> ♪

23:11.766 --> 23:16.521
♪ <i>Again</i> ♪

23:18.523 --> 23:21.568
♪ <i>Again...</i> ♪

23:21.651 --> 23:24.487
<i>She didn't talk much about that time,</i>

23:24.571 --> 23:26.781
<i>and I didn't push.</i>

23:26.865 --> 23:29.075
<i>I knew it was too painful.</i>

23:32.662 --> 23:36.791
But she said there wasn't
a single night that went by

23:36.875 --> 23:38.835
when she didn't dream about you.

23:38.918 --> 23:43.548
♪ <i>Am I dressed in others' sins?</i> ♪

23:46.551 --> 23:47.802
♪ <i>Hold my breath</i> ♪

23:47.886 --> 23:52.223
♪ <i>Until I'm honest</i> ♪

23:52.307 --> 23:55.101
♪ <i>Will I ever breathe again?</i> ♪

23:55.185 --> 23:57.187
What year was she released?

23:57.270 --> 23:58.897
'85.

23:58.980 --> 24:01.983
♪ <i>Am I looking</i> ♪

24:02.067 --> 24:06.571
♪ <i>For revival?</i> ♪

24:06.654 --> 24:10.075
♪ <i>Am I dressed in others' sin?</i> ♪

24:12.160 --> 24:15.413
♪ <i>Hold my breath...</i> ♪

24:15.497 --> 24:19.959
Laurel only had enough money
for a one-way bus ticket.

24:20.043 --> 24:22.295
♪ <i>Will I ever breathe again?</i> ♪

24:22.379 --> 24:24.923
<i>She thought about going to find you,</i>

24:25.006 --> 24:29.344
<i>but I think she was still</i>
<i>punishing herself.</i>

24:29.427 --> 24:33.139
<i>She felt she forfeited</i>
<i>the right to be your mother,</i>

24:33.223 --> 24:36.559
<i>so she went to the only place she knew.</i>

24:39.479 --> 24:41.398
♪ <i>Hold my breath</i> ♪

24:41.481 --> 24:46.069
♪ <i>Until I'm honest</i> ♪

24:46.152 --> 24:50.657
♪ <i>Will I ever breathe again?</i> ♪

24:52.742 --> 24:57.497
♪ <i>Will I ever breathe again?</i> ♪

24:59.499 --> 25:03.169
♪ <i>Will I ever breathe again?</i> ♪

25:06.131 --> 25:08.883
You have nothing to be ashamed of.

25:10.969 --> 25:12.971
I do.

25:16.266 --> 25:18.226
I had a child, Aunt Mae.

25:20.395 --> 25:23.773
I had a baby with a man who loved me.

25:25.108 --> 25:26.943
A boy.

25:31.489 --> 25:33.658
I don't know where he is.

25:38.496 --> 25:41.708
He used to give me gardenias.
(chuckles)

25:44.294 --> 25:46.004
Who?

25:46.087 --> 25:47.839
Raymond Blanchard.

25:47.922 --> 25:50.342
I didn't know gardenias were my favorite

25:50.425 --> 25:52.719
till he gave them to me.

25:54.220 --> 25:57.349
I loved him more than life.

25:59.017 --> 26:01.853
But I was so young.

26:01.936 --> 26:04.105
So naive.

26:05.190 --> 26:08.735
Naive enough to think that
a married man could be mine.

26:10.236 --> 26:12.489
That's why I was...

26:12.572 --> 26:14.991
happy when I got pregnant.

26:17.452 --> 26:21.623
I thought that would bind us together,

26:21.706 --> 26:24.167
make us a family.

26:24.250 --> 26:26.044
What happened?

26:27.128 --> 26:28.755
(inhales deeply)

26:28.838 --> 26:31.716
I lost 'em both.
(exhales)

26:33.593 --> 26:35.553
And it changed me.

26:38.682 --> 26:42.894
I let my broken heart be all that I was.

26:42.977 --> 26:46.898
And after that, my parents sent me away.

26:48.775 --> 26:50.777
But I came here.

26:52.404 --> 26:54.364
Found salvation.

26:58.785 --> 27:01.830
Oh, we should call your parents.

27:01.913 --> 27:03.415
I'm not ready.

27:03.498 --> 27:06.042
Oh, they... they need to know you're back.

27:07.544 --> 27:09.254
They're better off.

27:09.337 --> 27:11.423
No.

27:11.506 --> 27:14.759
I was no good as a daughter
and I'm no good as a mother.

27:14.843 --> 27:16.970
Hey, stop that talk.

27:19.097 --> 27:21.850
My son is gonna grow up
thinking I didn't love him.

27:21.933 --> 27:23.727
No.

27:23.810 --> 27:26.479
(sobbing):
Why couldn't I be good for him?

27:26.563 --> 27:28.148
Why?

27:29.232 --> 27:33.069
You can't keep doing this to yourself.

27:34.779 --> 27:38.533
If you don't let the guilt go,

27:38.616 --> 27:40.493
it'll strangle you.

27:42.078 --> 27:43.872
(whispers):
It will.

27:43.955 --> 27:45.957
♪ ♪

27:51.796 --> 27:53.798
(night bird calling)

28:09.689 --> 28:11.691
♪ ♪

28:35.256 --> 28:36.841
(screams)

28:43.682 --> 28:47.060
Come on, now, <i>cher,</i>
I'll give you a quarter.

28:48.645 --> 28:51.564
Now, why you want to give me
a hard time, huh?

28:51.648 --> 28:53.191
Either you want the onions or you don't.

28:53.274 --> 28:54.859
She don't never smile, does she?

28:54.943 --> 28:57.070
Leave me out of it, Woodrow.

28:57.153 --> 28:58.405
Fine.

28:58.488 --> 29:00.573
(sucks teeth)
Mm.

29:01.658 --> 29:03.201
Appreciate you.

29:05.161 --> 29:06.871
He's right, you know?

29:06.955 --> 29:08.540
About what?

29:08.623 --> 29:10.792
I miss that big smile of yours.

29:10.875 --> 29:12.544
I'm not sure what there is to smile about.

29:12.627 --> 29:13.795
Your health, for one.

29:13.878 --> 29:15.922
And me, for another.

29:17.007 --> 29:18.383
I know.

29:18.466 --> 29:20.385
I-I'm sorry, I...

29:20.468 --> 29:22.804
I just can't find a reason to...

29:43.658 --> 29:44.993
<i>BETH:</i>
<i>All right.</i>

29:45.076 --> 29:46.453
Time-out.

29:46.536 --> 29:49.080
So all y'all did was wave?

29:49.164 --> 29:50.248
All that hot sexual tension,

29:50.331 --> 29:51.583
-and the only...
-(Randall groans)

29:51.666 --> 29:52.917
I'm sorry, but there was hot sexual...

29:53.001 --> 29:55.128
There wasn't much we could do.

29:55.211 --> 29:57.005
<i>I was married.</i>

29:57.088 --> 29:59.174
<i>My wife was pregnant.</i>

29:59.257 --> 30:01.092
<i>And I hadn't seen Laurel in so long.</i>

30:01.176 --> 30:04.637
So yes, it was just a wave.

30:04.721 --> 30:06.973
At least that's how it was
for several years.

30:08.600 --> 30:10.977
<i>We had a few moments.</i>

30:11.061 --> 30:13.313
<i>Small but enough.</i>

30:14.814 --> 30:16.149
<i>RANDALL:</i>
<i>I'm sorry, Hai.</i>

30:16.232 --> 30:17.525
I'm a little lost.

30:17.609 --> 30:19.361
I thought you said
you and Laurel were close

30:19.444 --> 30:20.612
at the time she died.

30:20.695 --> 30:21.863
We were.

30:21.946 --> 30:25.075
But it took decades.

30:27.535 --> 30:29.621
<i>After my wife passed on</i>

30:29.704 --> 30:33.375
<i>and my children left home, it was just me.</i>

30:33.458 --> 30:36.753
<i>But knowing Laurel</i>
<i>was only a few feet away</i>

30:36.836 --> 30:38.922
<i>gave me comfort.</i>

30:42.467 --> 30:44.678
Until one day she was gone.

31:06.408 --> 31:07.784
Hi.

31:08.868 --> 31:10.870
Hi.

31:21.381 --> 31:23.341
When do you start treatment?

31:25.552 --> 31:27.637
I'm done with that.

31:30.432 --> 31:33.893
The doctor said it's an aggressive tumor.

31:33.977 --> 31:35.812
Meaning...

31:35.895 --> 31:37.564
there ain't no treatment.

31:38.857 --> 31:40.859
Oh, Laurel.

31:51.494 --> 31:53.413
Have you eaten today?

31:53.496 --> 31:55.457
No.

31:55.540 --> 31:57.417
But I'm-I'm gonna.

31:57.500 --> 31:59.002
I cook.

31:59.085 --> 32:00.712
You eat.

32:06.468 --> 32:08.470
♪ ♪

32:11.890 --> 32:13.641
<i>Her doctor was wrong.</i>

32:13.725 --> 32:16.311
<i>Or maybe God wanted us to have more time.</i>

32:17.312 --> 32:20.023
'Cause Laurel lived another two years.

32:20.106 --> 32:21.816
-It's hot.
-It's perfect. Okay, okay...

32:21.900 --> 32:23.818
(laughs)
All right, okay.

32:23.902 --> 32:26.446
♪ ♪

32:26.529 --> 32:28.782
(laughter)

32:28.865 --> 32:31.242
♪ ♪

32:31.326 --> 32:34.454
<i>I learned her story, learned your story.</i>

32:34.537 --> 32:37.874
<i>Every day with her was perfect.</i>

32:37.957 --> 32:39.959
♪ ♪

32:44.047 --> 32:46.007
If only we had more of them.

32:56.935 --> 32:58.937
(sighs)

33:00.730 --> 33:02.273
(door creaks open)

33:04.734 --> 33:07.237
(sniffles)

33:24.462 --> 33:26.256
What are you thinking about?

33:28.758 --> 33:30.760
My son.

33:37.225 --> 33:39.436
I wish I had told him.

33:41.354 --> 33:42.981
You'll get a chance to.

33:46.526 --> 33:48.528
♪ ♪

33:54.492 --> 33:57.871
-What a life.
-HAI: Hmm.

33:57.954 --> 33:59.706
It's strange.

33:59.789 --> 34:01.958
After all this time,

34:02.042 --> 34:04.336
I can still feel her here.

34:04.419 --> 34:06.755
Sometimes when I swim in the lake,

34:06.838 --> 34:09.007
I swear I could hear her laugh.

34:09.090 --> 34:10.884
(Hai chuckles)

34:10.967 --> 34:13.553
Mm, I have something for you.

34:15.555 --> 34:17.724
You know, Hai, you should
really consider making this

34:17.807 --> 34:20.352
into, like, a podcast
or, like, a book or something.

34:20.435 --> 34:23.438
You could call it <i>Alex Haley</i>
<i>Presents Laurel's Roots.</i>

34:23.521 --> 34:25.732
(laughter)

34:25.815 --> 34:27.942
These belong to you.

34:29.611 --> 34:31.112
Uh...

34:41.831 --> 34:43.625
You sure you don't want it?

34:43.708 --> 34:45.293
You've been looking after it for years.

34:45.377 --> 34:47.212
It's yours.

34:49.589 --> 34:51.841
(keys jingle)

34:51.925 --> 34:54.969
I don't know how to thank you for today.

34:55.053 --> 34:58.890
I waited a long time
to do this for Laurel.

34:58.973 --> 35:00.475
I should be thanking you.

35:02.310 --> 35:04.270
Okay.

35:04.354 --> 35:06.189
See you tomorrow at breakfast.

35:11.528 --> 35:13.154
(door closes)

35:13.238 --> 35:16.116
That was, uh...
(sighs)

35:18.827 --> 35:20.620
How are you holding up?

35:24.082 --> 35:26.418
-We own a farmhouse.
-We own a farmhouse.

35:26.501 --> 35:27.627
By a lake.

35:27.711 --> 35:28.670
Mm-hmm.

35:28.753 --> 35:29.838
In New Orleans.

35:31.297 --> 35:35.468
Where my dead biological mother grew up.

35:35.552 --> 35:37.595
And fell in love

35:37.679 --> 35:41.307
with her Vietnamese boyfriend.

35:43.727 --> 35:46.271
That's how I'm holding up.

35:48.148 --> 35:50.942
I could go for a shot
of the absinthe if you...

35:51.026 --> 35:52.861
you know...

35:52.944 --> 35:54.821
Maybe the whole bottle.

35:54.904 --> 35:56.906
(both laugh)

36:02.871 --> 36:04.873
♪ ♪

36:25.060 --> 36:26.978
♪ ♪

36:58.009 --> 37:00.011
♪ ♪

37:28.790 --> 37:30.792
♪ ♪

37:52.063 --> 37:54.065
♪ ♪

38:03.199 --> 38:05.201
(woman laughs)

38:06.411 --> 38:09.414
WOMAN:
My baby.

38:18.548 --> 38:20.967
My baby.

38:32.479 --> 38:35.482
I didn't even know I was looking for you.

38:36.941 --> 38:39.861
Now I've found you, and you're gone.

38:39.944 --> 38:41.946
I'm sorry.

38:43.531 --> 38:45.450
I'm sorry.

38:45.533 --> 38:47.369
I wish...

38:47.452 --> 38:50.538
I wish I could change everything.

38:52.332 --> 38:56.211
But I can't, and you know that.

38:56.294 --> 38:59.214
And all this sadness

38:59.297 --> 39:01.758
is weighing you down.

39:04.177 --> 39:07.055
(chuckles softly)
You have my eyes.

39:09.724 --> 39:12.977
I see so much pain in them.

39:14.062 --> 39:16.064
Aren't you tired?

39:21.653 --> 39:24.781
You need to let the pain go.

39:28.868 --> 39:30.954
I don't know how.

39:32.038 --> 39:34.040
Yes, you do.

39:44.634 --> 39:46.636
(screaming)

40:04.696 --> 40:08.241
<i>Me yêu con.</i>

40:09.617 --> 40:11.536
What is that?

40:11.619 --> 40:14.539
Something I've been...

40:14.622 --> 40:17.625
wanting to say to you for a long time.

40:19.044 --> 40:21.296
I love you.

40:25.717 --> 40:28.720
I love you.

40:32.307 --> 40:34.309
I love you, too.

40:38.146 --> 40:39.773
♪ ♪

41:03.797 --> 41:05.298
What?
(chuckles)

41:06.383 --> 41:08.301
You seem different.

41:08.385 --> 41:09.844
Lighter.

41:09.928 --> 41:12.222
(chuckles)

41:16.226 --> 41:19.104
I know my birth story, Beth.

41:20.188 --> 41:24.526
And it's not just
getting left at a fire station.

41:26.611 --> 41:28.613
It's two people.

41:30.031 --> 41:33.034
Two imperfect people...

41:34.619 --> 41:37.038
...that loved me.

41:42.877 --> 41:44.796
I'm-a call Kevin.

41:45.880 --> 41:47.090
What, now?

41:47.173 --> 41:51.678
I don't want to hold on
to the bad stuff anymore.

41:53.179 --> 41:54.681
I want to let it all go.

41:56.182 --> 41:57.767
Okay.

42:02.188 --> 42:04.399
-(line rings)
<i>-KEVIN: Randall, hey.</i>

42:04.482 --> 42:06.985
<i>RANDALL: Hey, Kev.</i>
<i>We're driving home from New Orleans.</i>

42:07.068 --> 42:08.903
<i>Uh, long story.</i>

42:08.987 --> 42:11.197
-I was wondering if we could talk.
<i>-I-I'm sorry, Randall.</i>

42:11.281 --> 42:12.657
Listen, I can't right now, okay?

42:12.741 --> 42:15.285
My whole life has been turned upside down.

42:15.368 --> 42:18.621
Madison's in labor,
and I'm stuck here in Vancouver.

42:18.705 --> 42:20.623
<i>I'm trying to get home</i>
<i>in time for the birth,</i>

42:20.707 --> 42:22.334
<i>but she's already at the hospital, and...</i>

42:22.417 --> 42:23.418
she's all alone.

42:23.501 --> 42:25.003
I never...

42:25.086 --> 42:26.588
never should've come here.

42:26.671 --> 42:27.797
Hey, Kev...

42:27.881 --> 42:29.341
No, l... I'm sorry.
I'll-I'll call you soon.

42:29.424 --> 42:31.426
Okay? I'm sorry.

